OL,3,CMinister accused of breaching human
OL,4,Crights law in teachers' pay dispute
OL,6,FTreasury Minister has been accused of
OL,7,Fbreaching human rights law after she
OL,8,Fcontroversially wrote directly to
OL,9,Fteachers in a bid to end their long-
OL,10,Frunning dispute over pay.
OL,12,Fstated that teachers would
OL,13,Fautomatically be given the
OL,14,FGovernment's latest offer and then
OL,15,Fbanned from taking part in any
OL,16,Findustrial action relating to pay
OL,17,Funtil 2027, unless they opted out by
OL,18,Fmidday on Thursday 1 February.
